-- RBS to invest $1.6 billion on services to corporate customers
-- By Matt Scuffham
-- Mon Sep 29, 2014 11:08AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 29 (Reuters) - State-backed Royal Bank of Scotland <RBS.L> said on Monday it would invest over 1 billion pounds ($1.6 billion) to improve services for its commercial and corporate customers.

The bank said the investment would result in simpler and quicker services for customers including account opening and lending, with most lending decisions being made within 5 days.